text: The area of Kayabe District in Oshima Subprefecture. is a district located in Oshima Subprefecture, Hokkaido, Japan. As of 2004, the district has an estimated population of 24,463 and a density of 51.09 persons per km². The total area is 478.82 km². == Towns == *Mori *Shikabe ==Mergers== *On December 1, 2004 the town of Minamikayabe was merged into the expanded city of Hakodate. *On April 1, 2005 the town of Sawara merged into the town of Mori. title: Kayabe District, Hokkaido
